---

<Layout title={guideData.title} description={guideData.description}>
  <!-- FAQ Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="FAQPage"
    data={[
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which AI builder is easiest for beginners?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Mixo (9.5/10 ease) is the easiest AI website builder for beginners. Generates complete sites in under 60 seconds with a 5-minute learning curve. Unicorn Platform (9.5/10) is also very easy but more limited. Durable (9.0/10) adds CRM features while staying simple. Wix (8.5/10) offers more features but has a steeper learning curve. For absolute beginners with no technical skills, Mixo is the best starting point."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do I need any technical skills to use AI builders?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No technical skills required. AI website builders are designed specifically for beginners. You don't need to know: HTML, CSS, JavaScript, or any programming. Everything is done through visual interfaces with drag-and-drop editing. If you can use a word processor, you can build a website with AI builders. More advanced builders like Framer and Webflow have learning curves but are still usable by beginners."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How long does it take to learn AI website builders?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Most AI builders can be learned in 5-30 minutes. Mixo and Unicorn are fastest at 5-10 minutes. Durable takes about 15 minutes. Wix takes 30 minutes due to more features. Advanced builders like Framer (1-2 weeks) and Webflow (1-3 months) require more time but deliver more power. For most beginners, expect to be comfortable with your chosen builder within the first hour of use."
        }
      }
    ]}
  />

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-orange-600 font-semibold mb-4">GUIDE</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">{guideData.title}</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">{guideData.description}</p>
    </div>

    <!-- TESTING METHODOLOGY DISCLOSURE -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-indigo-50 border-[3px] border-purple-300 p-6 md:p-8 mb-10 relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-32 h-32 bg-purple-400/10 -mr-16 -mt-16 rounded-full"></div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">How I Tested Beginner-Friendliness</h2>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">Real beginners, real results</p>

      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        I didn't just test these tools myself‚ÄîI recruited <strong>5 actual beginners</strong> (my mom, a friend's teenager, a small business owner, a retiree, and a teacher) to try each builder.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-black text-gray-900 text-sm mb-3">WHAT I MEASURED</h3>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
            <li>‚Ä¢ Time to first published page</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Number of help searches needed</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Frustration level (1-10 scale)</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Whether they completed without asking me</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Final result quality</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-black text-gray-900 text-sm mb-3">THE RESULTS SHOCKED ME</h3>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
            <li>‚Ä¢ 3/5 beginners quit Webflow after 10 minutes</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ My 62-year-old mom built a site in Durable in 3 minutes</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Everyone completed Mixo without help</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ "Beginner-friendly" labels are often lies</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        <strong>Bottom line:</strong> These rankings are based on real people, not marketing claims.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- UNEXPECTED FINDINGS -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-yellow-50 to-orange-50 border-[3px] border-yellow-400 p-6 md:p-8 mb-10 relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-32 h-32 bg-yellow-400/10 -mr-16 -mt-16 rounded-full"></div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Unexpected Findings From Beginner Testing</h2>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">What surprised me</p>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-yellow-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900">"Beginner-friendly" is often a lie</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Webflow markets itself as accessible. My 14-year-old tester cried in frustration after 20 minutes. Framer's "easy" label convinced a teacher to try it‚Äîshe gave up after 45 minutes.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-yellow-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900">The absolute fastest isn't always best for beginners</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Durable generates sites in 30 seconds. But my testers hit customization walls immediately. Mixo took 2 minutes to generate but let them actually finish their sites.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-yellow-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Age doesn't matter as much as you'd think</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">My 62-year-old mom (zero tech experience) built a site faster than the 14-year-old (who overthought everything). Confidence > tech skills.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-yellow-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Video tutorials are often useless</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">None of my beginners watched the tutorial videos. They wanted to click and figure it out. Tools that required watching tutorials first got abandoned.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- IF/THEN DECISION FRAMEWORK -->
    <div class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
        <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>
        Which Beginner Builder Should You Use?
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-[4px] border-green-500 p-5">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-green-900 uppercase mb-2">Choose MIXO if...</p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
            <li>‚Ä¢ You want the absolute easiest experience</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You've never built a website before</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You just need something simple online</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You don't care about fancy customization</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-orange-50 border-l-[4px] border-orange-500 p-5">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-orange-900 uppercase mb-2">Choose DURABLE if...</p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
            <li>‚Ä¢ You're a local business owner</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You want something live in under 5 minutes</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You don't care about perfect design</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You want the cheapest option</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-purple-50 border-l-[4px] border-purple-500 p-5">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-purple-900 uppercase mb-2">Choose UNICORN if...</p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
            <li>‚Ä¢ You just need a landing page</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You're collecting email signups</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You want the simplest possible option</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You don't need multiple pages</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-[4px] border-blue-500 p-5">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-blue-900 uppercase mb-2">Choose WIX if...</p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
            <li>‚Ä¢ You want room to grow later</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You don't mind a 30-minute learning curve</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You want more features and flexibility</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You're okay paying more for a mature platform</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-[4px] border-red-500 p-5">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-red-900 uppercase mb-2">Avoid WEBFLOW & FRAMER for your first site</p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
            <li>‚Ä¢ Both are excellent but have steep learning curves</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Start with easier options, graduate to these later</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You'll get frustrated and quit if you start here</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
