            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-red-600 mt-1">‚óè</span><span><strong>Technical jargon:</strong> Confusing terminology</span></li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-red-600 mt-1">‚óè</span><span><strong>No AI features:</strong> Manual setup required</span></li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-red-600 mt-1">‚óè</span><span><strong>Poor support:</strong> Limited help resources</span></li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-red-600 mt-1">‚óè</span><span><strong>Code required:</strong> Needs HTML/CSS knowledge</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Beginner Tips -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Tips for Beginner Success</h2>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-6">
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
          <li><strong>Start simple:</strong> Don't try to build everything at once. Start with basic pages and expand.</li>
          <li><strong>Use templates:</strong> Pre-made templates are designed to work well. Customize rather than building from scratch.</li>
          <li><strong>Watch tutorials:</strong> Most builders have video tutorials. Watch a few before starting.</li>
          <li><strong>Take your time:</strong> There's no rush. Build at your own pace.</li>
          <li><strong>Ask for help:</strong> Support teams are there to help. Use them.</li>
          <li><strong>Test thoroughly:</strong> Preview your site before publishing. Check mobile view too.</li>
          <li><strong>Keep backups:</strong> Most builders save automatically, but duplicate your site before major changes.</li>
          <li><strong>Learn gradually:</strong> Start with basics, learn advanced features as you gain confidence.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

